text: Would usually come here for the Japanese food. First time try the Chinese stall. Nice, the 辣子鸡 Chongqing chicken is even better than most restaurant.

Quite a good mix of stalls over here. Had the Japanese food. The salmon and ikura Don was fresh and the rice was good. The keisen chirashi Don was also very fresh. The presentation of the Wasabi was beautiful.
The coffee shop had very good coffee and tea. The people preparing the drinks were very professional at performing their task.
The only complaint here is that service was quite slow and internet connection was not good.
pork sumiyaki don (9.50) from japanese stall is to die for, drinks from kopifellas are outstanding but they close at like 6pm, try not to come when nearby gess dismisses at around 3

Fantastic, freshly made sushi!
Tokyo Taste @ Dairy farm Mall food court.

Can warmly recommend the spicy salmon maki and the gyoza.
Awesome!!!!!!

Not too bad a place for afternoon lunch. Quiet area at dairy farm cuz this mall is new. But nice place to hang out after a walk at the hill next door. This place is rather small with 7 outlets only. But I like the Japanese stall with nice chirashi bowl. I also love the kopifella stall. They sell the best tea and coffee to me. Love it.
